-- These parameters back the AgentToolInputsEditor inline UI on the Agent Tool
-- Selection step (Step 39). The editor's values feed Step 39's prompt template
-- placeholders ({agent_sql_catalog}, {agent_tool_sql_mcp_enabled}, etc.) so the
-- generated prompt produces docs/agent_tool_plan.yaml with user-confirmed tool
-- backends. Step 44 (Tools and MCP) then reads that plan to wire the tools.
-- SQL MCP is the only family enabled by default (samples.wanderbricks with
-- all-tables scope, governed by Unity Catalog permissions). Genie, Vector
-- Search, UC Functions, and External MCP are opt-in via per-family checkboxes
-- so users only fill in IDs for the tools they actually want.

